</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF76DB12CB182FC0731ED47AB" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F76DB12CB182FC07369E4787" blockId="24.[151,1437,907,1330]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F76DB12CB182FC0732C2474D" box="[199,251,1016,1042]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: There is no indication in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76DB12CB3E5FC0831994753" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[672,928,1015,1042]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 104)</bibRefCitation>
that there was more than a single specimen available, rather he states that he had no access to any female: “ 
<emphasis id="B9598714F76DB12CB239FBE431DD4777" box="[892,996,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">f# ignota</emphasis>
”. In Sundevall’s acquisition catalogue there is a reference to a single specimen, and in his list of duplicates the species is not mentioned. The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76DB12CB465FBC037BB471B" box="[1312,1410,1087,1113]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">holotype</typeStatus>
is NRM 568777 [6752a], a male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F76DB12CB312FB9C3122473F" box="[599,795,1123,1149]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" value="1840-02-11">
11 February 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F76DB12CB3A6FB9C3122473F" box="[739,795,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Pietermaritzburg. This was supported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76DB12CB442FB9C330247E3" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="24" pageNumber="545" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 40–41)</bibRefCitation>
, who also identified it as a juvenile specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76DB12CB228FB7836FE47E3" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[877,1223,1159,1185]" class="Aves" family="Cisticolidae" genus="Cisticola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="natalensis" subSpecies="natalensis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76DB12CB228FB7836FE47E3" box="[877,1223,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">Cisticola natalensis natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76DB12CB593FB7733744784" authority="Sundevall, 1850" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Drymoica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloris">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76DB12CB593FB7737A547E3" box="[1238,1436,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">Drymoica chloris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76DB12CB1D2FB5433744784" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[151,333,1195,1222]" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is thus a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76DB12CB240FB53369A4787" authority="A. Smith, 1843" authorityName="A. Smith" authorityYear="1843" box="[773,1187,1195,1221]" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Drymoica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76DB12CB240FB5331D74787" box="[773,1006,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="545">Drymoica natalensis</emphasis>
A. Smith, 1843
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
